Gut morphology (worker). Crop small. Mixed segment with one large and one small mesenteric lobe (the small one is vestigial in
L. brevilabius
). Malpighian tubules inserted in two pairs at the junction of mesenteron and proctodeum, between the mesenteric lobes. Proctodeum very large. First segment (P 1 ) strongly dilated, about the same size as the third (P 3 or paunch). Enteric valve wide. Armature with 1–6 ridges of irregular sizes covered with short and straight or long and curved, hair­like spines.
